WEBVTT

00:02.160 --> 00:03.366
OLIVER:
Previously on Arrow:

00:03.600 --> 00:07.207
Maybe I'm finally ready to admit
that I still have feelings for you too.

00:07.440 --> 00:11.081
No. Malcolm is planning
to level the Glades.

00:11.320 --> 00:13.448
My father,
he told me that he failed the city.

00:13.640 --> 00:15.529
But I never knew what he meant
until now.

00:15.720 --> 00:18.166
Merlyn's plan is what I returned
from the island to stop.

00:24.320 --> 00:25.606
Oh, no.

00:29.480 --> 00:33.963
You can survive this.
Make it home. And make it better.

00:35.000 --> 00:36.889
Right my wrongs.

00:45.000 --> 00:47.128
- Dad.
- Survive.

00:48.960 --> 00:50.325
[GUNSHOT]

00:51.800 --> 00:53.802
[OLIVER PANTING]

01:03.560 --> 01:05.209
I hope I didn't hurt you.

01:07.640 --> 01:11.804
At least I can properly thank you now
for saving my life.

01:12.200 --> 01:14.885
If I only knew...

01:15.080 --> 01:18.289
...how you were spending
your nights.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.560
My hope is that I can explain
everything to you...

01:22.760 --> 01:24.762
...to help you understand.

01:24.960 --> 01:26.405
You murdered my father.

01:27.600 --> 01:30.285
You sentenced me to that island...

01:30.520 --> 01:32.761
...to five years of hell.

01:34.440 --> 01:37.489
I'm truly sorry
for what happened to you.

01:40.040 --> 01:42.088
You know I have lost people.

01:42.280 --> 01:44.044
Yeah, your wife.

01:44.240 --> 01:46.163
Do you really think...

01:46.360 --> 01:49.762
...that you're honoring
Tommy's mother...

01:50.000 --> 01:52.606
...by destroying the Glades?

01:52.840 --> 01:54.126
As surely as you believe...

01:54.320 --> 01:56.402
...you're honoring your father
with this hood.

01:58.600 --> 02:02.002
Not a day goes by
I don't miss your father.

02:03.120 --> 02:04.804
You'll see him soon.

02:10.080 --> 02:12.401
You can't beat me, Oliver.

02:12.960 --> 02:15.281
Yes, you're younger
and you're faster.

02:15.480 --> 02:17.881
Yet you always seem
to come up short against me.

02:19.240 --> 02:20.685
Want to know why?

02:21.600 --> 02:24.001
Because you don't know...

02:24.280 --> 02:27.682
...in your heart,
what you're fighting for.

02:29.080 --> 02:32.323
What you're willing to sacrifice,
and I do.

02:37.040 --> 02:38.769
No one can stop
what's about to come.

02:43.080 --> 02:45.447
Not even the vigilante.

03:00.280 --> 03:03.682
Plane's holding steady at 33,000 feet.
The range for missile intercept.

03:06.960 --> 03:08.883
Lock missile one on target.

03:10.080 --> 03:12.048
Missile one locked
on the jet's heat trail.

03:12.800 --> 03:15.007
FRYERS:
Prepare to launch on my mark.

03:15.200 --> 03:17.123
DURAND:
Yes, sir.

03:23.440 --> 03:24.646
[YELLING]

03:25.280 --> 03:26.645
[DURAND GRUNTS]

03:33.560 --> 03:35.881
Fire! Fire the missile now!

03:55.400 --> 03:56.640
[GRUNTS]

04:12.520 --> 04:13.851
[GROANS]

04:22.000 --> 04:23.365
[NECK SNAPS]

04:33.360 --> 04:34.691
[CRACKS]

04:38.080 --> 04:39.411
[GUNSHOT]

04:42.760 --> 04:46.128
I take back every joke about you
sticking a tracking device in your boot.

04:55.160 --> 04:56.685
Felicity's
at Queen Consolidated.

04:56.880 --> 04:59.531
She's going through data
she pulled off Merlyn's network.

04:59.720 --> 05:01.165
- Did she find anything?
- Yeah.

05:01.400 --> 05:03.687
The design schematics
of the earthquake generator.

05:03.880 --> 05:05.041
So we can shut it down.

05:05.280 --> 05:06.725
Assuming we find it in time.

05:06.880 --> 05:07.881
[PHONE RINGS]

05:09.280 --> 05:11.681
DIGGLE: Yeah, Felicity, I got him.
- Thank God.

05:11.880 --> 05:14.042
- Is he okay?
DIGGLE: Mostly.

05:14.240 --> 05:16.891
Okay. I'm on my way.

05:17.120 --> 05:19.327
LANCE:
Miss Smoak.

05:23.120 --> 05:25.248
Where are you off to
in such a hurry?

05:30.240 --> 05:31.924
Please.

05:34.240 --> 05:35.605
Take a seat.

05:35.800 --> 05:37.529
You know, I think I'd rather stand.

05:39.960 --> 05:43.487
- You're not exactly a hardened criminal.
- No, I'm not any kind of criminal.

05:43.640 --> 05:46.530
- What do you call computer hacking?
- A hobby?

05:47.760 --> 05:50.650
That I do not engage in.

05:50.840 --> 05:52.285
Hey, I got a whole mess...

05:52.480 --> 05:55.484
...of gobbledygook I don't understand
but it says otherwise.

05:56.720 --> 06:00.327
I had my tech guy scrub through
your computer at Queen Consolidated.

06:00.520 --> 06:03.046
You used it to hack into
Blackhawk Squad Security...

06:03.200 --> 06:06.044
...research arrows shipped
to a company called Sagittarius...

06:06.200 --> 06:09.283
...and to analyze a water sample
to tie back to a Vertigo drug lab.

06:09.480 --> 06:10.811
These are all cases...

06:11.000 --> 06:13.162
...involving...

06:13.360 --> 06:14.441
...The Hood.

06:15.120 --> 06:16.724
Tell me, Felicity.

06:17.560 --> 06:18.641
What am I thinking?

06:20.600 --> 06:21.965
[PHONE RINGS]

06:22.120 --> 06:24.122
Saved by the bell.

06:24.480 --> 06:25.720
Excuse me.

06:28.880 --> 06:30.882
HOOD: Hello, detective.
- Funny you should call.

06:31.320 --> 06:34.802
- I got your sidekick sitting in front of me.
HOOD: I don't have a sidekick.

06:35.000 --> 06:37.207
When I need help, I call you.

06:37.400 --> 06:40.244
Merlyn plans to level the Glades
with a manmade earthquake...

06:40.440 --> 06:42.568
...using technology
from Unidac Industries.

06:46.120 --> 06:47.485
What?

06:47.640 --> 06:50.405
Ha, ha. Now you're trying
to have fun with me.

06:50.560 --> 06:54.167
I don't know Merlyn's timetable. You need
to evacuate the Glades immediately.

06:54.320 --> 06:56.209
Get as many people
to safety as you can.

06:56.400 --> 07:00.564
Whatever you think of me,
detective, please...

07:01.200 --> 07:02.247
...believe this.

07:06.120 --> 07:08.805
Sounds like you have
bigger problems than me.

07:14.200 --> 07:16.282
Don't leave town.

07:21.000 --> 07:22.490
You know...

07:23.360 --> 07:27.126
...I used to think the vigilante was
a criminal too but it seems to me...

07:27.320 --> 07:31.370
...whoever he is, he's willing to sacrifice
to help the people of this city.

07:34.080 --> 07:36.003
Kind of makes him a hero.

07:36.200 --> 07:37.565
Doesn't it?

07:48.840 --> 07:50.763
Look who it is.

07:51.520 --> 07:55.730
- My best friend in life.
- Hey, buddy.

07:57.640 --> 07:58.971
I took your advice, you know.

08:00.640 --> 08:03.849
I went to Laurel's
to fight for her.

08:04.760 --> 08:09.243
So imagine my surprise
seeing you there, kissing her.

08:10.640 --> 08:12.847
- I'm sorry.
- No, you're not.

08:16.440 --> 08:19.250
Something's happening
and it involves your father.

08:19.440 --> 08:23.331
- Keep my father out of this.
- Our fathers.

08:24.240 --> 08:26.846
They aren't the men
we thought they were.

08:27.400 --> 08:30.006
They made a plan together...

08:30.320 --> 08:31.924
...to destroy the Glades.

08:34.320 --> 08:37.289
Do you have any idea
what you sound like right now?

08:37.480 --> 08:39.801
Your father's gonna do it.

08:41.240 --> 08:43.811
Because he thinks
it will avenge your mother's death.

08:44.039 --> 08:45.929
Do not talk about my mother.

08:54.560 --> 08:56.688
The difference...

08:57.160 --> 08:59.003
...between us, Tommy...

08:59.200 --> 09:02.682
...is that I didn't find out
the truth about my father...

09:02.880 --> 09:05.167
...until it was too late.

09:06.240 --> 09:07.571
But you've always known...

09:08.320 --> 09:10.209
...deep down...

09:10.440 --> 09:14.809
...you have always known
the man he is.

09:19.000 --> 09:21.480
I wish you would have died
on that island.

09:46.240 --> 09:47.446
Open.

09:48.320 --> 09:49.845
[YELLING]

09:55.720 --> 09:57.245
We need to reprogram
the missile.

09:57.440 --> 09:58.885
I don't know how to reprogram.

10:01.800 --> 10:03.484
- I do.
- Hey, Shado!

10:07.280 --> 10:08.611
[GRUNTS]

10:18.200 --> 10:19.486
Oliver, put the chip in.

11:09.280 --> 11:13.046
Quick, I got a comm stat meeting in five.
I don't want to be late for my funeral.

11:13.240 --> 11:15.447
I've got it under good authority
that Merlyn...

11:15.640 --> 11:18.450
...plans to level the Glades
using an earthquake device...

11:18.640 --> 11:20.130
...made by Unidac Industries.

11:20.360 --> 11:24.331
- Who's your source in all this?
- The vigilante.

11:26.600 --> 11:27.647
He called me.

11:28.360 --> 11:31.011
Yeah, has done
the last few months.

11:31.520 --> 11:33.602
He's been helpful
on some cases.

11:33.800 --> 11:35.723
You asked for the task force
to catch him.

11:35.960 --> 11:39.043
- You swore you'd bring him in.
- I know. I swore to uphold the law.

11:39.200 --> 11:42.204
The law is steady and unchanging.
The law needed to be protected.

11:43.760 --> 11:48.482
But what are laws, rules,
if they don't protect people?

11:49.400 --> 11:51.971
I'm throwing away
my career by telling you this...

11:52.160 --> 11:57.041
...I am willing to sacrifice catching this guy
if it means saving people's lives.

11:58.200 --> 11:59.281
Please.

12:02.600 --> 12:04.329
You're suspended.

12:05.480 --> 12:07.005
Leave your gun and badge
with the duty sergeant.

12:07.240 --> 12:10.608
- Lieutenant--
- Suspension or incarceration.

12:10.800 --> 12:12.484
You choose.

12:31.200 --> 12:32.929
No more lies, Mom.

12:33.480 --> 12:35.209
The Undertaking.

12:35.640 --> 12:36.926
We need to stop it.

12:37.720 --> 12:40.371
Everything I have ever said
or done...

12:40.560 --> 12:43.131
...has been to protect you
and your sister.

12:44.280 --> 12:46.203
What about all those people
in the Glades?

12:46.400 --> 12:47.561
I'm not their mother.

12:49.400 --> 12:52.324
- I spoke to Malcolm.
- You what?

12:55.360 --> 12:56.771
He could have killed you.

12:59.440 --> 13:01.124
He killed your father.

13:02.880 --> 13:04.325
No, he didn't.

13:05.480 --> 13:10.725
After the Gambit went down,
dad and I both made it to the life raft.

13:11.240 --> 13:14.164
And then we drifted, for days.

13:14.800 --> 13:18.885
In the end, there wasn't enough
food and water for both of us.

13:22.240 --> 13:24.368
So he shot himself in the head.

13:24.560 --> 13:26.369
I don't want to hear this.

13:26.560 --> 13:29.404
He sacrificed himself.

13:29.600 --> 13:31.011
So that I could live.

13:31.240 --> 13:32.969
Do you really think...

13:33.840 --> 13:35.444
...that I could go on living...

13:35.640 --> 13:40.965
...knowing that you sacrificed
thousands more in my name?

13:42.440 --> 13:44.841
Mom. Please.

13:45.760 --> 13:49.321
You have to help me
stop Malcolm.

13:49.520 --> 13:52.763
We need to know where the device is.

13:54.640 --> 13:56.642
[PHONE RINGING]

14:04.760 --> 14:06.569
Malcolm.

14:07.840 --> 14:08.887
How can I help you?

14:12.440 --> 14:14.329
I see.

14:15.360 --> 14:18.011
Yes, thank you for calling.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.402
- What is it?
- Malcolm's accelerated his timetable.

14:22.600 --> 14:24.887
The Undertaking is...

14:26.120 --> 14:27.451
---haPDening tonight.

14:30.720 --> 14:32.404
Where are you going?

14:36.960 --> 14:40.760
Somebody in this family
needs to put an end to this.

14:42.960 --> 14:45.122
Whatever the cost.

14:59.000 --> 15:00.445
LAUREL:
Hi.

15:05.320 --> 15:06.890
Hey-

15:08.240 --> 15:09.924
LAUREL:
I woke up and you were gone.

15:10.160 --> 15:12.891
I'm really sorry about that.

15:13.240 --> 15:16.926
Oliver, I'm trying not to think
that our history's repeating.

15:17.160 --> 15:20.084
- That you're scared again.
- No.

15:21.800 --> 15:22.847
That's not it.

15:23.840 --> 15:26.525
Then will you tell me
what's going on with you?

15:31.280 --> 15:33.760
There are so many things...

15:33.960 --> 15:36.531
...that I have wanted to tell you...

15:36.720 --> 15:38.245
...for so long.

15:41.680 --> 15:44.081
I never told you what happened to me
on the island.

15:44.720 --> 15:46.722
You didn't have to.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.048
I can see that it changed you.

15:49.520 --> 15:52.888
That's the thing.
Laurel, it didn't.

15:53.800 --> 15:56.770
Those five years didn't change me.
They just...

15:57.200 --> 16:02.286
...they scraped away
all the things that I wasn't...

16:02.520 --> 16:06.525
...and revealed the person
I always was, which is the person--

16:09.080 --> 16:10.764
That's who you always saw.

16:12.520 --> 16:15.729
I don't know how you saw it,
but you did.

16:15.920 --> 16:20.084
Nobody in my life
is who I thought they were.

16:20.320 --> 16:21.560
Except you.

16:37.440 --> 16:40.091
Laurel, I need you
to do something for me.

16:40.280 --> 16:43.250
- Stay out of the Glades tonight.
- Why?

16:44.040 --> 16:46.042
You'll know soon.

16:47.000 --> 16:48.411
One way or the other.

16:50.440 --> 16:52.010
I have to go.

17:03.640 --> 17:05.050
It's over.

17:05.280 --> 17:07.601
Laurel and me, I mean.

17:07.800 --> 17:11.088
She's with Oliver, again.
Always.

17:11.280 --> 17:12.520
I'm sorry, son.

17:12.800 --> 17:17.328
Yeah, and he said you wanted to nuke
the Glades or something.

17:19.400 --> 17:22.050
It's funny, Scotch doesn't make it
any more believable.

17:22.920 --> 17:26.606
Maybe after your jihad,
we can, uh, grab some steaks.

17:30.600 --> 17:31.806
It's true, Tommy.

17:32.960 --> 17:35.247
It's the reason
I closed your mother's clinic.

17:35.880 --> 17:37.370
I didn't wanna see it leveled.

17:40.440 --> 17:41.680
What?

17:41.880 --> 17:44.645
I have something
I'd like you to listen to.

17:48.160 --> 17:50.447
The night your mother died...

17:52.320 --> 17:53.321
...she called me.

17:55.200 --> 17:56.725
I awoke to a voice-mail from her.

17:57.120 --> 18:01.921
- Dad.
- Her final gift to me.

18:03.240 --> 18:06.608
REBECCA [ON RECORDING]:
Malcolm, I 'm in trouble.

18:06.840 --> 18:09.320
I told, I told him
to take everything.

18:09.520 --> 18:11.363
My 1110/79)”-

18:11.840 --> 18:13.649
...my Ting-.

18:14.040 --> 18:15.371
Turn it off.

18:15.520 --> 18:16.760
REBECCA:
They shot me.

18:16.960 --> 18:18.883
I screamed for help...

18:19.080 --> 18:21.447
-...but no one would come. God.
- No one would come.

18:21.640 --> 18:25.611
REBECCA:
Malcolm, I don't want to die alone.

18:27.480 --> 18:32.361
She bled out into the pavement
while people passed and did nothing.

18:34.960 --> 18:38.885
Your mother built her clinic in the Glades
because she wanted to save this city.

18:40.000 --> 18:42.128
It can't be saved.

18:42.800 --> 18:46.885
Because the people there
don't want it to be saved.

18:47.560 --> 18:49.562
- So you kill them all--?
- Yes!

18:49.760 --> 18:52.604
They deserve to die!
All of them!

18:52.800 --> 18:55.167
The way she died!

19:02.400 --> 19:04.289
The Undertaking
is happening tonight.

19:07.320 --> 19:09.004
Felicity may have found something.

19:10.640 --> 19:13.325
This symbol is the map
of the old subway tunnel system.

19:13.520 --> 19:16.569
That's got us thinking the Undertaking
is connected to the Glades.

19:16.800 --> 19:19.041
- What if it's more specific?
- What do you mean?

19:19.240 --> 19:22.164
If I had a machine that could trigger
an earthquake...

19:22.400 --> 19:25.768
...in an otherwise geologically stable area,
where would I position it?

19:27.320 --> 19:29.561
- Underground.
- Yeah.

19:31.080 --> 19:32.764
This is a U.S. geological survey...

19:32.960 --> 19:35.691
...of the tectonic plates
running underneath Starling City.

19:35.920 --> 19:39.447
This red line here is a known fault
that runs right below the Glades.

19:39.600 --> 19:42.285
About a mile. Fault runs under
the old 10th Street subway.

19:42.560 --> 19:45.689
Dollars to doughnuts, the seismic device
is somewhere along there.

19:45.920 --> 19:47.445
I know where it is.

19:49.120 --> 19:51.122
[PHONE VIBRATES]

19:53.440 --> 19:54.726
Now is not a good time.

19:54.960 --> 19:56.371
Yeah, understate much?

19:56.560 --> 19:59.325
Mom has a whole bunch
of reporters here.

19:59.520 --> 20:03.320
She's holding a press conference
or something.

20:03.960 --> 20:05.200
What channel?

20:05.640 --> 20:06.971
It looks like all of them.

20:07.520 --> 20:10.444
Felicity, pull up the local news,
please.

20:12.480 --> 20:14.084
My name is Moira Dearden Queen.

20:14.280 --> 20:18.410
I am the acting CEO
of Queen Consolidated.

20:18.600 --> 20:21.683
And God forgive me,
I have failed this city.

20:22.800 --> 20:26.168
For the past five years,
under the threat for my life...

20:26.360 --> 20:28.761
...and the lives of my family...

20:30.080 --> 20:31.525
...I have been complicit...

20:31.720 --> 20:35.361
...in an undertaking
with one horrible purpose.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.571
To destroy the Glades
and everyone in it.

20:43.400 --> 20:45.482
I realize now
that my family's safety...

20:45.680 --> 20:49.605
...will mean nothing
if I let this dreadful act occur.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.570
But you need to know...

20:52.040 --> 20:56.090
...that the architect
of this nightmare...

20:57.600 --> 20:58.931
...is Malcolm Merlyn.

20:59.800 --> 21:00.847
[SCREAMS]

21:01.320 --> 21:03.926
Yes, and I have proof
that he has killed dozens...

21:04.120 --> 21:06.088
...in pursuit of this madness.

21:06.320 --> 21:08.800
Adam Hunt, Frank Chen...

21:09.000 --> 21:10.684
...and my husband...

21:12.040 --> 21:13.690
...Robert.

21:19.200 --> 21:20.247
Please.

21:20.880 --> 21:23.804
If you reside in the Glades,
you need to get out now.

21:24.520 --> 21:27.808
Your lives and the lives
of your children depend on it.

21:28.880 --> 21:30.405
Please.

21:33.640 --> 21:35.642
[REPORTERS YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

21:37.840 --> 21:41.447
- I don't understand.
- I'm sorry. I love you.

21:41.640 --> 21:43.642
- I love Roy.
- Roy?

21:43.840 --> 21:46.366
He lives in the Glades.

21:46.800 --> 21:49.201
- I can't leave him there.
- Sweetheart. Thea.

21:49.400 --> 21:51.562
HILTON: You're under arrest
for conspiracy to murder.

21:51.760 --> 21:53.842
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

21:54.080 --> 21:55.809
You have the right to an attorney.

21:56.080 --> 21:58.162
TOMMY:
Is it true?

21:58.920 --> 22:00.968
Did you kill all those people?

22:02.840 --> 22:04.490
I did What I had to do.

22:31.640 --> 22:33.130
OFFICER:
Freeze!

22:33.400 --> 22:35.607
Malcolm Merlyn,
you are under arrest.

22:37.400 --> 22:38.447
Don't move.

22:42.320 --> 22:43.481
Dad, no.

22:48.440 --> 22:50.044
Please, Dad.

22:52.000 --> 22:53.490
Stay back.

22:53.840 --> 22:55.126
I don't want to hurt you.

22:55.400 --> 22:57.209
You can't.

22:57.680 --> 22:59.569
And you can't stop me.

23:03.640 --> 23:05.210
FELICITY:
Oliver, I'm sorry.

23:07.040 --> 23:08.849
Don't be.

23:09.120 --> 23:12.044
She gave those people a chance.

23:12.520 --> 23:14.284
I thought Merlyn broke your bow.

23:18.320 --> 23:20.243
I have another.

23:23.560 --> 23:25.449
I was going over
the device schematics.

23:25.640 --> 23:27.847
The device can be set
for a timed detonation...

23:28.000 --> 23:31.891
-...or remote activated by mobile transmitter.
- Something Merlyn could have on him.

23:32.080 --> 23:34.447
If we can just get our hands
on this transmitter...

23:34.680 --> 23:37.923
-...we don't need to track down the device.
-It's too big an if.

23:38.160 --> 23:39.446
I need you in the subway.

23:39.680 --> 23:43.446
- Find the device, disarm it.
- So you can take on Merlyn by yourself?

23:45.160 --> 23:47.686
- I have to.
- Oh, he'll kill you, Oliver.

23:50.440 --> 23:51.566
I know.

23:54.600 --> 23:57.251
He's beaten me twice.

23:58.080 --> 24:00.048
And I don't know how to stop him.

24:02.240 --> 24:05.005
Okay. How about this time,
you bring along something...

24:05.160 --> 24:07.367
...you didn't have
the last time you two fought.

24:08.080 --> 24:09.525
- Me.
- I can't let you.

24:09.720 --> 24:11.722
I can't let you do this
by yourself, man.

24:12.720 --> 24:16.042
Oliver, you are not alone, not since
you brought me into this.

24:17.840 --> 24:19.080
Us into this.

24:22.280 --> 24:23.725
Besides, Army regulations.

24:24.120 --> 24:26.566
A soldier never lets a brother
go into battle alone.

24:33.720 --> 24:35.927
- I'm out of bows.
- I got my gun.

24:36.160 --> 24:38.731
I guess it's up to me
to do the dismantling.

24:38.920 --> 24:40.445
This whole area is ground zero.

24:40.640 --> 24:42.130
I want you out of here.

24:42.320 --> 24:44.607
If you're not leaving,
I'm not leaving.

24:45.120 --> 24:47.646
Besides, if I don't deactivate
the device, who will?

24:57.440 --> 24:59.329
[PHONE RINGS]

24:59.480 --> 25:00.561
You were right.

25:00.760 --> 25:02.250
I need one more thing from you.

25:02.440 --> 25:06.570
- Yeah? What do I got left to give?
- I know where Merlyn is keeping the device.

25:07.240 --> 25:10.562
It's in an abandoned subway station
near Pap Street.

25:10.760 --> 25:14.890
LANCE: How do you know?
- That's where his wife was murdered.

25:15.080 --> 25:18.289
[OVER PHONE] I need someone I can trust
to deactivate the device.

25:20.840 --> 25:24.606
We have a mutual friend that I think
could talk you through it.

25:25.120 --> 25:27.600
She says you care
about the people of this city...

25:27.800 --> 25:29.450
...that it needs you.

25:30.200 --> 25:32.487
Right now, detective...

25:33.680 --> 25:35.170
...it needs you.

25:43.200 --> 25:45.202
[YELLING]

25:49.720 --> 25:52.849
REPORTER [ON TV]: Earlier today,
Moira Queen, CEO of Queen Consolidated...

25:53.040 --> 25:55.964
...admitted to a conspiracy
to destroy the Glades.

25:56.160 --> 25:59.323
Everyone within a five-mile radius
has been asked to evacuate.

25:59.800 --> 26:00.801
MAN [OVER PA]:
Stay calm.

26:01.000 --> 26:04.482
Do not rush and do not panic.

26:27.640 --> 26:30.962
Proceed out of the Glades
in an orderly manner.

26:36.520 --> 26:37.851
[GRUNTING]

26:54.520 --> 26:56.568
Looks like we missed him.

27:03.360 --> 27:04.691
Shade .

27:05.760 --> 27:07.524
Sade.

27:27.160 --> 27:29.083
[SLADE LAUGHING]

27:30.560 --> 27:32.927
Oh, I should have figured.

27:33.560 --> 27:36.086
You couldn't save the day...

27:36.680 --> 27:40.048
-...without making a mess.
- Where's Shado?

27:40.720 --> 27:42.927
- I thought she was with you.
FRYERS: Actually...

27:44.480 --> 27:45.766
...she's with me.

27:46.240 --> 27:48.686
Let her go. It's over, Fyers.

27:54.720 --> 27:56.165
Let her go.

27:56.840 --> 27:58.205
Amazing.

27:58.440 --> 28:00.727
A two-year operation undone...

28:00.920 --> 28:04.447
...because a young playboy
happened to wash up on the shore...

28:04.600 --> 28:07.763
...and now here you are, a killer.

28:09.240 --> 28:12.449
You wanted nothing more
than to leave this island...

28:12.640 --> 28:13.971
...and now you can.

28:14.160 --> 28:17.607
I can call in a rescue ship,
you can go home.

28:17.840 --> 28:19.683
Tell me, Mr. Queen.

28:19.960 --> 28:23.726
Are you prepared to sacrifice
your freedom for her?

28:38.240 --> 28:39.890
Guess so.

28:52.680 --> 28:54.011
[COUGHING NEARBY]

28:55.400 --> 28:57.004
Tommy.

28:57.480 --> 29:00.689
- Tommy.
- Oliver.

29:02.200 --> 29:03.486
Where's your father?

29:04.720 --> 29:05.767
I don't know.

29:07.200 --> 29:08.247
You were right.

29:09.200 --> 29:12.761
- You were right about him.
DIGGLE: Oliver.

29:17.040 --> 29:18.201
Are you gonna kill him?

29:22.880 --> 29:24.882
Get to safety.

29:33.440 --> 29:35.442
Looks like a false wall.

29:46.600 --> 29:47.726
Welcome, gentlemen.

29:47.920 --> 29:49.445
I've been waiting for you.

29:49.680 --> 29:52.126
I wanted to see you
watch your city die.

29:52.320 --> 29:55.642
- Where's the transmitter?
- Somewhere I can easily get to it.

29:55.840 --> 29:58.241
I doubt it. You'll be too dead.

30:17.320 --> 30:18.845
[GROANS]

30:23.240 --> 30:26.130
Stairs, Oliver. Go, go.

30:31.400 --> 30:34.802
So tell me, are you ready to die?

30:37.200 --> 30:40.329
FELICITY: You found it yet, detective?
- I'm not sure what I'm looking for.

30:40.600 --> 30:41.840
You want me to describe it?

30:43.920 --> 30:45.968
No, I got it.

30:51.600 --> 30:55.002
FELICITY: You should see something that
looks like a circuit board. Pull it out.

30:56.280 --> 30:58.567
Do you see a timer?

31:00.160 --> 31:01.366
Seven minutes.

31:01.560 --> 31:04.211
Okay. Well, the good news is...

31:04.400 --> 31:07.006
...this is going to be
a paperweight in three.

31:07.200 --> 31:09.931
MAN [OVER PA]:
Everyone leave the Glades. I repeat...

31:10.720 --> 31:12.324
...leave the Glades now.

31:12.520 --> 31:14.284
MAN 1: What do you got there, grandpa?
- Hey.

31:14.440 --> 31:16.966
MAN 2: Please, please, it's all I have.
ROY: Hey.

31:19.080 --> 31:21.321
Hey. Back off.

31:21.560 --> 31:23.881
Learn how to count, jerkwad.
There's three of us.

31:24.080 --> 31:25.411
Oh, is that right?

31:35.280 --> 31:37.442
- Because I only count one.
- With a gun.

31:43.040 --> 31:45.850
- Where did you learn how to do that?
- I have wicked aim.

31:47.400 --> 31:48.526
I went to your house.

31:48.760 --> 31:51.525
I figured I'd run for my life
with everyone else. Did you...?

31:51.720 --> 31:53.688
- Did you come to rescue me?
- Yeah.

31:55.080 --> 31:56.650
Come on.

32:14.840 --> 32:15.841
[ARROW BEEPS]

32:18.360 --> 32:21.045
Look for three wires,
you need a green one...

32:21.840 --> 32:23.649
...a yellow and one blue.

32:23.840 --> 32:26.525
- Cut the blue one.
- All right, I got it, I got it.

32:27.440 --> 32:28.965
[WHIRRING]

32:33.680 --> 32:35.569
Oh, my God.

32:39.240 --> 32:41.971
LANCE: No, no, no.
- There must be an anti-tamper safeguard.

32:42.160 --> 32:44.447
Hold on. Fm gonna figure out
how to override it.

32:46.200 --> 32:48.123
Not enough time.
There's not enough time.

32:48.360 --> 32:50.886
- Just hold on.
LANCE: Not enough time.

32:54.240 --> 32:56.322
- Laurel.
- Dad.

32:56.520 --> 33:00.320
Don't worry, I got your message
and I did not come into work today.

33:00.520 --> 33:02.568
Save it, kiddo,
we both know you're there.

33:02.760 --> 33:07.004
You got to get out of the Glades
right now. Okay, please.

33:08.040 --> 33:10.281
- Dad?
LANCE: Right now, Laurel.

33:10.480 --> 33:11.811
Right now, Laurel.

33:12.120 --> 33:13.929
Daddy, you're scaring me.

33:14.880 --> 33:16.848
Sorry, but I'm not...

33:18.080 --> 33:19.286
I'm not gonna make it.

33:19.800 --> 33:21.370
What?

33:22.120 --> 33:24.646
- What?
LANCE: You have to promise me one thing.

33:26.240 --> 33:27.730
You're not gonna die with me.

33:28.560 --> 33:30.961
[OVER PHONE]
You have to go on with your life.

33:31.160 --> 33:34.369
After your sister died, I pushed people away,
I became like a ghost.

33:34.560 --> 33:37.211
Didn't think I had the right to live
if my baby couldn't.

33:39.400 --> 33:42.449
Promise me you're not gonna make
the same mistakes as I did.

33:44.600 --> 33:47.126
Promise me, Laurel.

33:47.320 --> 33:49.084
[OVER PHONE]
Promise me.

33:50.720 --> 33:52.722
I promise.

34:01.080 --> 34:02.764
I love you, honey, now and forever.

34:03.600 --> 34:05.204
I love you.

34:07.240 --> 34:08.889
Dad.

34:11.080 --> 34:15.608
Detective Lance? I need
you to listen to me very carefully.

34:17.719 --> 34:20.485
You do know how dangerous it is
to text and drive, right?

34:20.679 --> 34:21.966
- It can wait.
- It can't.

34:22.159 --> 34:26.130
- I'm trying to find another route out of here.
- Let me. It's not worth the risk.

34:27.120 --> 34:28.406
Roy.

34:30.679 --> 34:31.806
Roy.

34:32.040 --> 34:34.360
Help me out.
Help me out. Help me out.

34:34.560 --> 34:36.847
Roy, stop.

34:37.040 --> 34:39.565
The device is about to go off
any second.

34:42.320 --> 34:46.405
- I can't leave any of them behind.
- I know you have something to prove.

34:46.639 --> 34:49.246
But you're not the vigilante.

34:49.480 --> 34:52.449
Look, I can't do this
unless I know you're safe.

34:53.360 --> 34:55.726
Then you better haul ass
out of here too.

35:35.560 --> 35:38.325
Don't struggle. It's over.

35:39.080 --> 35:41.242
There was never any doubt
in the outcome.

35:41.440 --> 35:45.445
Don't worry. Your mother and sister
will be joining you in death.

35:45.640 --> 35:47.130
ROBERT:
Survive.

35:54.720 --> 35:56.529
[MALCOLM GRUNTS]

36:03.800 --> 36:08.761
Thank you for teaching me
what I'm fighting for.

36:11.880 --> 36:13.484
But my father taught me how.

36:24.000 --> 36:25.570
Come on.

36:27.600 --> 36:28.840
[POWERS DOWN]

36:35.520 --> 36:37.648
FELICITY:
Oliver, Lance did it.

36:38.920 --> 36:40.604
It's over.

36:41.000 --> 36:45.642
If I've learned anything
as a successful businessman, it's...

36:45.800 --> 36:46.847
[COUGHS]

36:47.000 --> 36:49.321
"Redundancy.

36:49.480 --> 36:50.970
[GROANS]

37:00.480 --> 37:02.289
Felicity...

37:02.840 --> 37:06.049
...there's another device.
There's two of them.

37:15.280 --> 37:16.930
LANCE:
What the hell's happening?

37:20.960 --> 37:22.564
Okay, that's enough.

37:47.440 --> 37:49.204
I turned the damn thing off.

37:49.920 --> 37:52.605
Merlyn had a second device.

37:53.640 --> 37:56.644
Laurel. She's at CNRI.

37:57.840 --> 38:00.320
Go. Go!

38:19.720 --> 38:21.643
Laurel.

38:22.520 --> 38:25.808
- Oliver?
- Are you okay?

38:27.360 --> 38:28.964
Yeah.

38:30.240 --> 38:31.571
[S053]

38:33.400 --> 38:36.643
The damage seems to be contained
on the east side...

38:37.320 --> 38:40.529
-...past Wells Street.
- Laurel.

38:41.880 --> 38:45.282
- Are you gonna be okay?
- Go, Oliver. Go, go, go.

38:49.040 --> 38:51.407
Help. Please.

38:58.040 --> 39:00.691
Please! Help me!

39:02.720 --> 39:03.846
Tommy.

39:04.360 --> 39:05.600
What are you doing here?

39:05.800 --> 39:08.804
I kind of figured
that you might come back to CNRI.

39:09.000 --> 39:10.764
[TOMMY GRUNTING]

39:10.920 --> 39:13.002
You came here for me?

39:16.600 --> 39:18.329
I love you.

39:26.840 --> 39:29.446
Get up. Go. Go.
I'm right behind you.

39:31.480 --> 39:33.130
LANCE:
Laurel. Laurel.

39:33.520 --> 39:35.966
- Dad. Dad.
- Oh, sweetie.

39:40.400 --> 39:43.688
- No. No. Tommy!
- No. Laurel. Laurel.

39:43.880 --> 39:46.167
- No, you can't. You can't.
- I love him!

39:47.080 --> 39:48.366
Let go of me.

39:49.320 --> 39:53.723
It's too late. It's too late, it's too late.
I'm sorry.

39:56.800 --> 39:58.131
LAUREL:
Tommy!

39:58.320 --> 40:01.802
Please, I want to help him.

40:09.280 --> 40:12.124
- Get it off.
- Okay.

40:13.960 --> 40:15.246
You're gonna be fine.

40:15.440 --> 40:19.001
Another thing, unh,
we've got to disagree on.

40:27.560 --> 40:30.530
- Tommy.
-ls--? ls Laurel safe?

40:30.720 --> 40:33.007
Is Laurel safe?
I tried to get her out of here.

40:33.880 --> 40:38.761
Yeah, yeah, you did.
You saved her.

40:38.960 --> 40:41.440
All right, let me get you out of here.

40:41.640 --> 40:42.846
You're gonna be fine.

40:43.840 --> 40:45.524
Oliver, stop.

40:49.440 --> 40:51.841
I'm sorry.

40:52.040 --> 40:53.849
No. Don't apologize.

40:54.240 --> 40:55.969
I was angry.

40:56.160 --> 40:58.891
And I was jealous. I...

41:01.920 --> 41:03.160
I am my father.

41:03.800 --> 41:06.565
No. No, you're not.

41:07.680 --> 41:09.967
Did--? Did you kill him?

41:11.840 --> 41:13.524
No.

41:17.600 --> 41:21.525
- Thank you.
- No, no.

41:25.720 --> 41:27.449
Tommy.

41:32.000 --> 41:34.367
It should have been me.

41:35.960 --> 41:37.928
Open your eyes, Tommy.

41:43.760 --> 41:45.967
Open your eyes.

42:27.560 --> 42:29.562
[English - US - SDH]
